HEADWORD: Picamar
<hw>Pic"a*mar`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>pix</ets>,
<ets>picis</ets>, pitch + <ets>amarus</ets> bitter.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An oily liquid hydrocarbon extracted from the
creosote of beechwood tar. It consists essentially of certain
derivatives of pyrogallol.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

